text: Brandon Jennings (born September 23, 1989 in Compton, California) is an American former professional basketball player. He played parts of eleven seasons in the National Basketball Association (NBA). He played for the Milwaukee Bucks, Detroit Pistons, Orlando Magic, New York Knicks, and Washington Wizards. He played as a point guard. for the Milwaukee Bucks of the National Basketball Association (NBA). He also played basketball in Italy for Lottomatica Roma of the Italian Lega A. He last played for Zenit Saint Petersburg of the VTB United League. He was released after only 10 games because he criticized the team's management in an Instagram post.
